org.apache.flink.runtime.operators.sort

类 PartialOrderPriorityQueue<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

        • org.apache.flink.runtime.operators.sort.PartialOrderPriorityQueue<T>
  • 所有已实现的接口:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Queue<T>

    public class PartialOrderPriorityQueue<T>
extends java.util.AbstractQueue<T>
implements java.util.Queue<T>
    This class implements a priority-queue, which maintains a partial ordering of its elements such that the least element can always be found in constant time. Put()'s and pop()'s require log(size) time.

      • adjustTop

        public final void adjustTop()
        Should be called when the Object at top changes values. Still log(n) worst case, but it's at least twice as fast to 
         {
        pq.top().change();
        pq.adjustTop();
 }
        instead of 
         {
        o = pq.pop();
        o.change();
        pq.push(o);
 }
